# StaticTypeScriptFile

Creates a [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/) file with automatic formatting using Prettier.

# Minimal Example

Creates a basic TypeScript file with automatic formatting.

```ts
import { StaticTypeScriptFile } from "alchemy/fs";

const file = await StaticTypeScriptFile("hello.ts", `
  export function hello(name: string) {
    return "Hello " + name;
  }
`);
```

# Component Example

Creates a TypeScript React component with proper formatting.

```ts
import { StaticTypeScriptFile } from "alchemy/fs";

const component = await StaticTypeScriptFile("Button.tsx", `
  interface Props {
    text: string;
    onClick: () => void;
  }

  export function Button({ text, onClick }: Props) {
    return <button onClick={onClick}>{text}</button>;
  }
`);
```

# Custom Path Example

Creates a TypeScript file at a specific path.

```ts
import { StaticTypeScriptFile } from "alchemy/fs";

const utils = await StaticTypeScriptFile("utils", 
  "src/utils/format.ts",
  `
    export function formatDate(date: Date): string {
      return date.toLocaleDateString();
    }
  `
);
```

